## Usage\par
\par
```tsx showLineNumbers\par
import \{\par
  Field,\par
  FieldContent,\par
  FieldDescription,\par
  FieldError,\par
  FieldGroup,\par
  FieldLabel,\par
  FieldLegend,\par
  FieldSeparator,\par
  FieldSet,\par
  FieldTitle,\par
\} from "@/components/ui/field"\par
```\par
\par
```tsx showLineNumbers\par
<FieldSet>\par
  <FieldLegend>Profile</FieldLegend>\par
  <FieldDescription>This appears on invoices and emails.</FieldDescription>\par
  <FieldGroup>\par
    <Field>\par
      <FieldLabel htmlFor="name">Full name</FieldLabel>\par
      <Input id="name" autoComplete="off" placeholder="Evil Rabbit" />\par
      <FieldDescription>This appears on invoices and emails.</FieldDescription>\par
    </Field>\par
    <Field>\par
      <FieldLabel htmlFor="username">Username</FieldLabel>\par
      <Input id="username" autoComplete="off" aria-invalid />\par
      <FieldError>Choose another username.</FieldError>\par
    </Field>\par
    <Field orientation="horizontal">\par
      <Switch id="newsletter" />\par
      <FieldLabel htmlFor="newsletter">Subscribe to the newsletter</FieldLabel>\par
    </Field>\par
  </FieldGroup>\par
</FieldSet>\par
```\par
\par
## Composition\par
\par
### Field\par
\par
A single control with label, helper text, and validation.\par
\par
```text\par
Field\par
\f1\u9500?\u9472?\u9472?\f0  FieldLabel\par
\f1\u9500?\u9472?\u9472?\f0  Input / Textarea / Switch / Select\par
\f1\u9500?\u9472?\u9472?\f0  FieldDescription\par
\f1\u9492?\u9472?\u9472?\f0  FieldError\par
```\par
\par
### FieldGroup\par
\par
Related fields in one group. Use `FieldSeparator` between sections when needed.\par
\par
```text\par
FieldGroup\par
\f1\u9500?\u9472?\u9472?\f0  Field\par
\f1\u9474?\f0    \f1\u9500?\u9472?\u9472?\f0  FieldLabel\par
\f1\u9474?\f0    \f1\u9500?\u9472?\u9472?\f0  Input / Textarea / Switch / Select\par
\f1\u9474?\f0    \f1\u9500?\u9472?\u9472?\f0  FieldDescription\par
\f1\u9474?\f0    \f1\u9492?\u9472?\u9472?\f0  FieldError\par
\f1\u9500?\u9472?\u9472?\f0  FieldSeparator\par
\f1\u9492?\u9472?\u9472?\f0  Field\par
    \f1\u9500?\u9472?\u9472?\f0  FieldLabel\par
    \f1\u9492?\u9472?\u9472?\f0  Input / Textarea / Switch / Select\par
```\par
\par
### FieldSet\par
\par
Semantic grouping with a legend and description, usually containing a `FieldGroup`.\par
\par
```text\par
FieldSet\par
\f1\u9500?\u9472?\u9472?\f0  FieldLegend\par
\f1\u9500?\u9472?\u9472?\f0  FieldDescription\par
\f1\u9492?\u9472?\u9472?\f0  FieldGroup\par
    \f1\u9500?\u9472?\u9472?\f0  Field\par
    \f1\u9474?\f0    \f1\u9500?\u9472?\u9472?\f0  FieldLabel\par
    \f1\u9474?\f0    \f1\u9500?\u9472?\u9472?\f0  Input / Textarea / Switch / Select\par
    \f1\u9474?\f0    \f1\u9500?\u9472?\u9472?\f0  FieldDescription\par
    \f1\u9474?\f0    \f1\u9492?\u9472?\u9472?\f0  FieldError\par
    \f1\u9492?\u9472?\u9472?\f0  Field\par
        \f1\u9500?\u9472?\u9472?\f0  FieldLabel\par
        \f1\u9492?\u9472?\u9472?\f0  Input / Textarea / Switch / Select\par
```\par
\par
## Anatomy\par
\par
The `Field` family is designed for composing accessible forms. A typical field is structured as follows:\par
\par
```tsx showLineNumbers\par
<Field>\par
  <FieldLabel htmlFor="input-id">Label</FieldLabel>\par
  \{/* Input, Select, Switch, etc. */\}\par
  <FieldDescription>Optional helper text.</FieldDescription>\par
  <FieldError>Validation message.</FieldError>\par
</Field>\par
```\par
\par
- `Field` is the core wrapper for a single field.\par
- `FieldContent` is a flex column that groups label and description. Not required if you have no description.\par
- Wrap related fields with `FieldGroup`, and use `FieldSet` with `FieldLegend` for semantic grouping.\par
\par
## Form\par
\par
See the [Form](/docs/forms) documentation for building forms with the `Field` component and [React Hook Form](/docs/forms/react-hook-form), [Tanstack Form](/docs/forms/tanstack-form), or [Formisch](/docs/forms/formisch).\par
