## Responsive Layout\par
\par
- **Vertical fields:** Default orientation stacks label, control, and helper text\f2\emdash ideal for mobile-first layouts.\par
- **Horizontal fields:** Set `orientation="horizontal"` on `Field` to align the label and control side-by-side. Pair with `FieldContent` to keep descriptions aligned.\par
- **Responsive fields:** Set `orientation="responsive"` for automatic column layouts inside container-aware parents. Apply `@container/field-group` classes on `FieldGroup` to switch orientations at specific breakpoints.\par
\par
<ComponentPreview\par
  styleName="radix-nova"\par
  name="field-responsive"\par
  previewClassName="h-[650px] p-6 md:h-[500px] md:p-10"\par
/>\par
\par
## Validation and Errors\par
\par
- Add `data-invalid` to `Field` to switch the entire block into an error state.\par
- Add `aria-invalid` on the input itself for assistive technologies.\par
- Render `FieldError` immediately after the control or inside `FieldContent` to keep error messages aligned with the field.\par
\par
```tsx showLineNumbers /data-invalid/ /aria-invalid/\par
<Field data-invalid>\par
  <FieldLabel htmlFor="email">Email</FieldLabel>\par
  <Input id="email" type="email" aria-invalid />\par
  <FieldError>Enter a valid email address.</FieldError>\par
</Field>\par
```\par
\par
## Accessibility\par
\par
- `FieldSet` and `FieldLegend` keep related controls grouped for keyboard and assistive tech users.\par
- `Field` outputs `role="group"` so nested controls inherit labeling from `FieldLabel` and `FieldLegend` when combined.\par
- Apply `FieldSeparator` sparingly to ensure screen readers encounter clear section boundaries.\par
\par
## API Reference\par
\par
### FieldSet\par
\par
Container that renders a semantic `fieldset` with spacing presets.\par
\par
| Prop        | Type     | Default |\par
| ----------- | -------- | ------- |\par
| `className` | `string` |         |\par
\par
```tsx\par
<FieldSet>\par
  <FieldLegend>Delivery</FieldLegend>\par
  <FieldGroup>\{/* Fields */\}</FieldGroup>\par
</FieldSet>\par
```\par
\par
### FieldLegend\par
\par
Legend element for a `FieldSet`. Switch to the `label` variant to align with label sizing.\par
\par
| Prop        | Type                  | Default    |\par
| ----------- | --------------------- | ---------- |\par
| `variant`   | `"legend" \\| "label"` | `"legend"` |\par
| `className` | `string`              |            |\par
\par
```tsx\par
<FieldLegend variant="label">Notification Preferences</FieldLegend>\par
```\par
\par
The `FieldLegend` has two variants: `legend` and `label`. The `label` variant applies label sizing and alignment. Handy if you have nested `FieldSet`.\par
\par
### FieldGroup\par
\par
Layout wrapper that stacks `Field` components and enables container queries for responsive orientations.\par
\par
| Prop        | Type     | Default |\par
| ----------- | -------- | ------- |\par
| `className` | `string` |         |\par
\par
```tsx\par
<FieldGroup className="@container/field-group flex flex-col gap-6">\par
  <Field>\{/* ... */\}</Field>\par
  <Field>\{/* ... */\}</Field>\par
</FieldGroup>\par
```\par
\par
### Field\par
\par
The core wrapper for a single field. Provides orientation control, invalid state styling, and spacing.\par
\par
| Prop           | Type                                         | Default      |\par
| -------------- | -------------------------------------------- | ------------ |\par
| `orientation`  | `"vertical" \\| "horizontal" \\| "responsive"` | `"vertical"` |\par
| `className`    | `string`                                     |              |\par
| `data-invalid` | `boolean`                                    |              |\par
\par
```tsx\par
<Field orientation="horizontal">\par
  <FieldLabel htmlFor="remember">Remember me</FieldLabel>\par
  <Switch id="remember" />\par
</Field>\par
```\par
\par
### FieldContent\par
\par
Flex column that groups control and descriptions when the label sits beside the control. Not required if you have no description.\par
\par
| Prop        | Type     | Default |\par
| ----------- | -------- | ------- |\par
| `className` | `string` |         |\par
\par
```tsx\par
<Field>\par
  <Checkbox id="notifications" />\par
  <FieldContent>\par
    <FieldLabel htmlFor="notifications">Notifications</FieldLabel>\par
    <FieldDescription>Email, SMS, and push options.</FieldDescription>\par
  </FieldContent>\par
</Field>\par
```\par
\par
### FieldLabel\par
\par
Label styled for both direct inputs and nested `Field` children.\par
\par
| Prop        | Type      | Default |\par
| ----------- | --------- | ------- |\par
| `className` | `string`  |         |\par
| `asChild`   | `boolean` | `false` |\par
\par
```tsx\par
<FieldLabel htmlFor="email">Email</FieldLabel>\par
```\par
\par
### FieldTitle\par
\par
Renders a title with label styling inside `FieldContent`.\par
\par
| Prop        | Type     | Default |\par
| ----------- | -------- | ------- |\par
| `className` | `string` |         |\par
\par
```tsx\par
<FieldContent>\par
  <FieldTitle>Enable Touch ID</FieldTitle>\par
  <FieldDescription>Unlock your device faster.</FieldDescription>\par
</FieldContent>\par
```\par
\par
### FieldDescription\par
\par
Helper text slot that automatically balances long lines in horizontal layouts.\par
\par
| Prop        | Type     | Default |\par
| ----------- | -------- | ------- |\par
| `className` | `string` |         |\par
\par
```tsx\par
<FieldDescription>We never share your email with anyone.</FieldDescription>\par
```\par
\par
### FieldSeparator\par
\par
Visual divider to separate sections inside a `FieldGroup`. Accepts optional inline content.\par
\par
| Prop        | Type     | Default |\par
| ----------- | -------- | ------- |\par
| `className` | `string` |         |\par
\par
```tsx\par
<FieldSeparator>Or continue with</FieldSeparator>\par
```\par
\par
### FieldError\par
\par
Accessible error container that accepts children or an `errors` array (e.g., from `react-hook-form`).\par
\par
| Prop        | Type                                       | Default |\par
| ----------- | ------------------------------------------ | ------- |\par
| `errors`    | `Array<\{ message?: string \} \\| undefined>` |         |\par
| `className` | `string`                                   |         |\par
\par
```tsx\par
<FieldError errors=\{errors.username\} />\par
```\par
\par
When the `errors` array contains multiple messages, the component renders a list automatically.\par
\par
`FieldError` also accepts issues produced by any validator that implements [Standard Schema](https://standardschema.dev/), including Zod, Valibot, and ArkType. Pass the `issues` array from the schema result directly to render a unified error list across libraries.\f0\par
